On March 18, 2009, the White House sent several nominations to the Senate for approval. The nominations included Russlynn Ali for Assistant Secretary for Civil Rights in the Department of Education, Susan Flood Burk as Special Representative of the President, Ashton B. Carter for Under Secretary of Defense for Acquisition, Technology, and Logistics, Carmel Martin for Assistant Secretary for Planning, Evaluation, and Policy Development in the Department of Education, James W. Miller for Under Secretary of Agriculture for Farm and Foreign Agricultural Services, and Charles P. Rose for General Counsel in the Department of Education.